 Indian Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940), ss. 5, 11, 30--These sections whether violated by r. III(3) of the Rules of Arbitration of the Indian Chamber of Commerce Calcutta--Said Rule empowering Registrar of Tribunal of Arbitration not to disclose names of arbitrators appointed by Chamber to a party who was not member of Chamber--Appointment of arbitrator whether not complete if name of arbitrator not disclosed to party-Commercial practice of not disclosing names--Justification for.
 
